HOUSE JOINT RESOLUTION 1064
By Russell
A RESOLUTION to honor the memory of Thomas Cory Myers
Gunnels.
WHEREAS, the members of this General Assembly were greatly saddened to learn of
the passing of Thomas Cory Myers Gunnels on March 24, 2021; and
WHEREAS, Cory Gunnels was an exemplary public servant and consummate
professional who worked assiduously to improve the quality of life for his fellow citizens in
numerous capacities; and
WHEREAS, born on May 12, 1982, Cory Gunnels was the son of our former colleague
Representative Doug Gunnels and Vicki Gunnels; and
WHEREAS, as a youngster, Cory and his brother, Brett, spent much of their childhood
years running in the halls of the State Capitol complex, making many friends, including
legendary Chief Sergeant at Arms of the House of Representatives Victor Thompson, who
dubbed them "my boys"; and
WHEREAS, after graduating from Greenback High School in 2000, Cory Gunnels
earned a Bachelor of Science degree in Business Administration from the University of
Tennessee in 2005; and
WHEREAS, on August 7, 2010, he was joined in holy matrimony with the love of his life,
Ashton Radcliff, and their joyous union was blessed on January 13, 2015, with one son, Cabe
Harley Gunnels, who was the apple of his father's eye; and
WHEREAS, Cory Gunnels had a passion for his family's farm and spent much of his
time there. An avid fan of the Tennessee Volunteers, he also loved hunting, fishing, gardening,
and traveling, especially out west to snowboard with his friends; and
HJR1064
014588
- 1 -

WHEREAS, a man of deep and abiding faith, Mr. Gunnels was a lifelong member of
Pine Grove Presbyterian Church, where friends and colleagues contributed $18,500 for the
construction of a new playground in his honor; and
WHEREAS, a devoted son, brother, father, and husband, Cory Gunnels leaves behind
an indelible legacy of integrity and probity in public life, compassion and loyalty in private life,
and diligence and dedication in all his chosen endeavors; and
WHEREAS, throughout his courageous battle with cancer, Cory Gunnels showed us all
what a real fighter looks like; he truly fought the good fight, finished the race, and kept the faith;
and
WHEREAS, it is fitting that the members of this General Assembly should pause to
remember the life of this exceptional gentleman and human being; now, therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES OF THE ONE HUNDRED
FOURTEENTH GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE SENATE
CONCURRING, that we honor the memory of Thomas Cory Myers Gunnels, reflecting fondly
upon his impeccable character and his stalwart commitment to living the examined life with
courage and conviction.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that we express our sympathy and offer our condolences
to the family of Mr. Gunnels.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that an appropriate copy of this resolution be prepared
for presentation with this final clause omitted from such copy and upon proper request made to
the appropriate clerk, the language appearing immediately following the State seal appear
without House or Senate designation.
